              ]
            }
          ],
          "INC-SOURCE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "incident_source": [
                  "D-T"
                ],
                "reaction": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " Water cooled Ti(T) target, bombarded with 3 MeV",
                " deuterons at 50 uAmp."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "ACTIV"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Vacuum extraction and gas counting of tritium.",
                " Activation reactions used as internal monitors."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                " A hemispherical compact geometry, diam 40 mm, was used",
                " for irradiations with the Ti(T) n source placed at the",
                " centre. Each sample was divided into three segments,",
                " and a Monte Carlo calculation was performed to",
                " calculate the neutron energy range seen by each",
                " segment, taking into account single (but not multiple)",
                " scattering in the tritium target, cooling water and",
                " surrounding capsule.",
                "     Angular range    neutron energy range",
                "     -------------    --------------------",
                "      0-40 degrees     19.02 +/- 0.56 MeV",
                "     40-65 degrees     17.68 +/- 0.77 MeV",
                "     65-82 degrees     16.32 +/- 0.58 MeV"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "PROPC"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Gas counting tube to measure tritium activity",
                " using low-level anticoincidence beta-counting in the",
                " gas phase."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "GELI"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " 32 Cm3 Ge(Li) detector to measure gamma",
                " activity induced by the monitor reactions.",
                " Proton recoil telescope 80 cm from the neutron source",
                " in the 130 degree direction, used as an external flux",
                " monitor."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "PART-DET": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "B-"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Beta particles from tritium decay."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "DG"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Decay gammas from monitor reactions."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "CORRECTION": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                " Neutron scattering in the tritium target,cooling water",
                " and the surrounding capsule"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ERR-ANALYS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "heading": "DATA-ERR",
                "minimum_value": null,
                "maximum_value": null,
                "correlation_property": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " Total error, formed by summing the",
                " statistical and systematic errors in quadrature."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "COMMENT": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Two external monitors were also used -",
                " 1) a proton recoil counter to measure the",
                "    neutron flux directly",
                " 2) the activity induced in a piece of cobalt",
                "    placed 25 cm from the neutron source in the",
                "    0 degree direction.",
                " All methods produced consistent results."
              ]
            }
          ],
